5
00:01:43.207 --> 00:01:45.000
(waves crashing)

6
00:01:51.256 --> 00:01:53.884
(somber music playing)

7
00:02:11.693 --> 00:02:14.446
(Vaemond Velaryon
speaking High Valyrian)

8
00:03:18.051 --> 00:03:19.720
(Daemon chuckling)

9
00:03:22.931 --> 00:03:26.310
♪ ♪

10
00:03:29.730 --> 00:03:32.107
(Vaemond continues)

11
00:03:59.217 --> 00:04:01.261
♪ ♪

12
00:04:27.120 --> 00:04:28.163
♪ ♪

13
00:04:35.003 --> 00:04:37.089
(indistinct chatter)

14
00:04:55.482 --> 00:04:58.527
Have you seen your father?

15
00:04:59.277 --> 00:05:02.280
Your little cousins
have lost their mother.

16
00:05:02.364 --> 00:05:03.990
They could use a kind word.

17
00:05:03.991 --> 00:05:05.074
I have an equal
claim to sympathy.

18
00:05:05.075 --> 00:05:07.827
- Jace.
- We should be at Harrenhal.

19
00:05:07.828 --> 00:05:09.830
mourning Lord Lyonel
and Ser Harwin.

20
00:05:11.081 --> 00:05:13.499
It would not be appropriate.

21
00:05:13.500 --> 00:05:17.254
The Velaryons are our kin
and the Strongs are not.

22
00:05:18.755 --> 00:05:20.048
Look at me.

23
00:05:20.632 --> 00:05:22.217
Do you understand?

24
00:05:29.224 --> 00:05:30.308
(indistinct chatter)

25
00:05:50.954 --> 00:05:52.497
Princess Helaena:
<i>Hand turns loom;</i>

26
00:05:52.581 --> 00:05:54.582
spool of green. spool of black;

27
00:05:54.583 --> 00:05:56.042
dragons of flesh

28
00:05:56.043 --> 00:05:59.504
weaving dragons of thread.

29
00:05:59.588 --> 00:06:02.924
Hand turns loom;
spool of green...

30
00:06:03.008 --> 00:06:05.343
- We have nothing in common.
- She's our sister.

31
00:06:05.427 --> 00:06:08.972
- You marry her. then.
- I would perform my duty.

32
00:06:09.056 --> 00:06:11.766
- if mother had
only betrothed us.
- (scoffs) If only.

33
00:06:11.767 --> 00:06:13.393
It would strengthen the family.

34
00:06:13.477 --> 00:06:14.353
Keep our Valyrian blood pure.

35
00:06:14.354 --> 00:06:17.981
- She's an idiot.
- She's your future queen.

36
00:06:20.233 --> 00:06:22.360
We actually do have

37
00:06:23.320 --> 00:06:24.946
one thing in common.

38
00:06:25.030 --> 00:06:28.533
We both fancy creatures
with very long legs.

39
00:06:30.702 --> 00:06:32.204
(claps hands)
Wench!

40
00:06:32.871 --> 00:06:35.832
- Another!
- Aegon.

41
00:06:35.916 --> 00:06:38.752
Dragon's flesh.
weaving dragons of thread.

42
00:06:42.464 --> 00:06:43.507
♪ ♪

43
00:06:47.761 --> 00:06:49.595
Lyonel Strong's son's
been staring at you

44
00:06:49.596 --> 00:06:51.598
since the moment we arrived.
Your Grace.

45
00:06:55.560 --> 00:06:57.145
Unabashedly.

46
00:06:58.438 --> 00:07:01.983
It is only a look of pride.
Ser Criston.

47
00:07:02.067 --> 00:07:03.527
Larys is the new
Lord of Harrenhal.

48
00:07:11.535 --> 00:07:14.329
♪ ♪

49
00:07:38.562 --> 00:07:41.564
Corlys Velaryon:
Both my seat and High Tide

50
00:07:41.565 --> 00:07:43.567
will be yours one day. Lucerys.

51
00:07:44.693 --> 00:07:47.695
Your brother will be king.
of course.

52
00:07:47.696 --> 00:07:50.323
He'll sit on endless
councils and ceremonies.

53
00:07:50.407 --> 00:07:53.076
but Lord of the Tides
rules the sea.

54
00:07:53.952 --> 00:07:55.203
Lucerys: Sorry.

55
00:07:55.287 --> 00:07:56.872
I don't want it.

56
00:08:00.167 --> 00:08:02.294
It's your birthright. lad.

57
00:08:06.381 --> 00:08:09.384
If I'm the Lord of Driftmark.
it means everyone's dead.

58
00:08:12.012 --> 00:08:15.056
♪ ♪

59
00:08:17.142 --> 00:08:20.061
- I'm very sorry.
- Thank you. Thank you.

60
00:08:42.918 --> 00:08:45.045
Rhaena: (crying)
Grandma...

61
00:08:49.341 --> 00:08:50.581
I don't want Mother to be gone.

62
00:08:57.849 --> 00:09:01.645
♪ ♪

63
00:09:17.035 --> 00:09:20.080
(indistinct chatter)

64
00:09:21.039 --> 00:09:24.376
(somber music)

65
00:09:29.256 --> 00:09:31.341
(dragon screeches)

66
00:09:41.226 --> 00:09:43.270
♪ ♪

67
00:10:05.667 --> 00:10:07.294
Retrieve your patron.

68
00:10:10.755 --> 00:10:11.798
Brother.

69
00:10:12.424 --> 00:10:15.135
(tense music playing)

70
00:10:27.105 --> 00:10:29.691
♪ ♪

71
00:10:32.986 --> 00:10:34.321
(sighs)

72
00:10:37.824 --> 00:10:39.784
♪ ♪

73
00:10:39.868 --> 00:10:41.703
(indistinct chatter)

74
00:10:53.256 --> 00:10:55.717
Your girls are the very
image of their mother.

75
00:10:57.093 --> 00:10:59.053
A comfort and an anguish.

76
00:10:59.054 --> 00:11:01.222
as I well remember.

77
00:11:02.140 --> 00:11:03.933
The gods can be cruel.

78
00:11:06.311 --> 00:11:08.480
It seems they've been
especially cruel to you.

79
00:11:09.481 --> 00:11:10.565
(chuckles) Yes.

80
00:11:12.942 --> 00:11:15.195
♪ ♪

81
00:11:26.122 --> 00:11:28.874
You should return with us
to King's Landing.

82
00:11:28.875 --> 00:11:30.543
It's time that you came home.

83
00:11:30.627 --> 00:11:32.504
Pentos is my home...

84
00:11:33.463 --> 00:11:36.091
- and that of my children.
- Daemon...

85
00:11:37.092 --> 00:11:39.552
I know we've had
our differences.

86
00:11:39.636 --> 00:11:40.916
but let them pass
with the years.

87
00:11:43.348 --> 00:11:45.391
There's a place for you
in my court

88
00:11:45.392 --> 00:11:46.786
if that's something
you should need.

89
00:11:46.810 --> 00:11:49.437
I need... nothing.

90
00:11:53.566 --> 00:11:54.609
♪ ♪

91
00:11:59.030 --> 00:12:02.075
Brother.

92
00:12:05.203 --> 00:12:08.247
I'm sorry for your loss.
my Prince.

93
00:12:08.248 --> 00:12:09.915
No matter how fat
the leech grows.

94
00:12:09.916 --> 00:12:11.918
it always wants
for another meal.

95
00:12:16.673 --> 00:12:18.716
♪ ♪

96
00:12:23.096 --> 00:12:23.721
Go to bed.

97
00:12:23.805 --> 00:12:26.474
- But. Mother...
- Go to bed.

98
00:12:37.360 --> 00:12:38.945
I'm going to bed. Aemma.

99
00:12:40.071 --> 00:12:43.658
Shall I see after
Queen Alicent.
Your Grace?

100
00:12:46.327 --> 00:12:48.662
No. Ser Harrold.

101
00:12:48.663 --> 00:12:50.707
You have the night's watch.
Ser Criston.

102
00:12:53.084 --> 00:12:54.961
Lord Commander.

103
00:13:00.133 --> 00:13:02.927
♪ ♪

104
00:13:07.432 --> 00:13:10.268
(indistinct chatter)

105
00:13:26.284 --> 00:13:27.576
(gasps)

106
00:13:27.577 --> 00:13:29.120
Brother?

107
00:13:30.497 --> 00:13:32.123
(Aegon grunts)

108
00:13:34.125 --> 00:13:35.710
Get to bed.

109
00:13:38.129 --> 00:13:41.174
♪ ♪

110
00:14:03.321 --> 00:14:07.074
(dragon calls)

111
00:14:07.075 --> 00:14:10.203
♪ ♪

112
00:14:21.381 --> 00:14:24.217
(dragon screeching)

113
00:14:37.981 --> 00:14:40.524
Rhaenys:
She wanted to come home

114
00:14:40.525 --> 00:14:42.485
and he denied her.

115
00:14:43.319 --> 00:14:46.030
Daemon did what he thought best.

116
00:14:47.073 --> 00:14:50.451
Daemon only ever does
what is best for Daemon.

117
00:14:51.995 --> 00:14:54.080
Laena needed our maesters.

118
00:14:59.460 --> 00:15:02.129
The surgeons in Pentos
are as well-trained

119
00:15:02.130 --> 00:15:05.258
as our maesters.

120
00:15:06.759 --> 00:15:10.554
You are looking to place blame

121
00:15:10.555 --> 00:15:12.724
for an act of the gods.

122
00:15:14.183 --> 00:15:16.227
Mayhaps the gods
have scorned us...

123
00:15:17.812 --> 00:15:20.982
for our insatiable pride.

124
00:15:26.821 --> 00:15:28.656
The crown was yours

125
00:15:28.740 --> 00:15:31.367
until those fools
at the Great Council

126
00:15:31.451 --> 00:15:33.119
plucked it from your head.

127
00:15:35.788 --> 00:15:37.706
Is it such a terrible thing

128
00:15:37.707 --> 00:15:39.458
for your husband
to wish to win it back?

129
00:15:39.459 --> 00:15:41.836
Tonight of all nights.
let us lay aside
this falsehood.

130
00:15:46.174 --> 00:15:47.341
It is not justice for
your wife that drives you.

131
00:15:47.342 --> 00:15:50.761
It is your own ambition.

132
00:15:50.762 --> 00:15:52.763
'Tis desire for the throne.

133
00:15:52.764 --> 00:15:55.266
if not for yourself.
then for the scions
of your house.

134
00:15:55.350 --> 00:15:58.686
I gave up the idea
of wearing a crown
a generation ago.

135
00:15:58.770 --> 00:15:59.853
It is you. lord husband.

136
00:15:59.854 --> 00:16:01.855
who refuses
to abandon this pursuit.

137
00:16:01.856 --> 00:16:04.692
even now.
at the cost of our children.

138
00:16:07.070 --> 00:16:08.863
(wind howling)

139
00:16:20.041 --> 00:16:22.460
What is this brief
mortal life...

140
00:16:23.252 --> 00:16:25.462
if not the pursuit of legacy?

141
00:16:25.463 --> 00:16:28.383
Legacy may be why you
live your life. Corlys.

142
00:16:39.894 --> 00:16:43.398
I want Driftmark
to pass through
Laena's line to Baela.

143
00:16:44.524 --> 00:16:47.360
To true Velaryon blood.

144
00:16:48.444 --> 00:16:50.571
Declare it now.
while all are gathered here.

145
00:16:50.655 --> 00:16:53.073
and we will say
that is how we will honor
Laena's memory.

146
00:16:53.074 --> 00:16:55.409
And disinherit our son?

147
00:16:55.410 --> 00:16:57.745
He will be the King Consort.

148
00:16:57.829 --> 00:16:58.829
His son will one day
sit the Iron Throne.

149
00:16:58.830 --> 00:17:02.541
You would have me cast
an even darker shadow

150
00:17:02.542 --> 00:17:03.542
over those little boys
than already exists.

151
00:17:03.543 --> 00:17:05.878
We are alone here. husband.

152
00:17:05.962 --> 00:17:08.006
You can speak the plain truth
as we both know it:

153
00:17:16.055 --> 00:17:18.349
Rhaenyra's children
are not of your blood.

154
00:17:26.315 --> 00:17:28.109
But Laena's are.

155
00:17:31.529 --> 00:17:33.614
They are her legacy.

156
00:17:34.741 --> 00:17:38.411
History does not remember blood.

157
00:17:43.124 --> 00:17:44.959
It remembers names.

158
00:17:55.887 --> 00:17:57.805
(footsteps retreating)

159
00:17:57.889 --> 00:18:00.558
- (waves crashing)
- (birds cawing)

160
00:18:05.354 --> 00:18:08.691
Rhaenyra:
Laenor has been
restless for years.

161
00:18:08.775 --> 00:18:12.486
but now. he will be useless.

162
00:18:12.487 --> 00:18:14.614
Or worse.

163
00:18:16.449 --> 00:18:21.203
I know better than anyone
that our marriage is a farce.

164
00:18:21.204 --> 00:18:25.041
But I at least make the effort
to maintain appearances.

165
00:18:26.542 --> 00:18:28.335
You have more to lose.

166
00:18:28.336 --> 00:18:32.924
Yes. well. that has been
my lot since my father
named me heir.

167
00:18:34.634 --> 00:18:37.011
We did try...

168
00:18:38.721 --> 00:18:40.055
to conceive a child.

169
00:18:40.056 --> 00:18:44.393
We performed our duty
as best we could.

170
00:18:47.104 --> 00:18:48.689
But to no avail.

171
00:18:55.780 --> 00:18:57.824
There was no joy in it.

172
00:19:01.744 --> 00:19:03.830
I found that elsewhere.

173
00:19:05.957 --> 00:19:09.335
- It felt good to be desired.
- Hm.

174
00:19:11.003 --> 00:19:14.465
I understand
Ser Harwin was quite...

175
00:19:16.634 --> 00:19:18.469
devoted to you.

176
00:19:20.596 --> 00:19:22.098
Yes. he was.

177
00:19:23.975 --> 00:19:25.560
And I trusted him.

178
00:19:30.690 --> 00:19:33.170
Should've forbidden
Ser Harwin from returning
to the Riverlands.

179
00:19:35.695 --> 00:19:36.797
Harren's curse is said
to be as strong now

180
00:19:36.821 --> 00:19:38.947
as it was after the Conquest.

181
00:19:38.948 --> 00:19:40.407
That's a ghost story.

182
00:19:40.408 --> 00:19:43.035
one Ser Otto and the Queen
would gladly exploit.

183
00:19:43.119 --> 00:19:47.582
I do not believe Alicent
capable of cold murder.

184
00:19:48.749 --> 00:19:51.752
Mm.

185
00:19:51.836 --> 00:19:54.297
Each of us is capable
of depravity.

186
00:19:55.131 --> 00:19:57.967
And more than you would believe.

187
00:20:01.429 --> 00:20:03.264
I believe it of you.

188
00:20:05.641 --> 00:20:07.201
If you're accusing me
of some depravity.

189
00:20:07.268 --> 00:20:09.395
you'll need to be more specific.

190
00:20:10.563 --> 00:20:13.316
I've been alone.

191
00:20:14.609 --> 00:20:15.859
- You abandoned me.
- I spared you.

192
00:20:15.860 --> 00:20:19.488
- You were a child.
- Yes.

193
00:20:19.572 --> 00:20:21.156
Yes. I was a child.

194
00:20:21.157 --> 00:20:23.993
And look at what my life
became without you.

195
00:20:25.661 --> 00:20:30.415
- Droll tragedy.
- Oh. and I wonder what you
think of mine by comparison?

196
00:20:30.416 --> 00:20:33.502
I know little of it.

197
00:20:37.757 --> 00:20:39.383
Did you love her?

198
00:20:42.053 --> 00:20:43.930
We were happy enough.

199
00:20:45.264 --> 00:20:48.017
Well. that in itself
is a great achievement.

200
00:20:52.897 --> 00:20:55.775
- I am sorry.
- Don't be.

201
00:20:57.902 --> 00:21:00.363
I am at least allowed
to mourn my losses.

202
00:21:25.596 --> 00:21:27.431
(light music playing)

203
00:21:30.810 --> 00:21:32.269
Rhaenyra.

204
00:21:37.566 --> 00:21:39.402
I'm no longer a child.

205
00:21:58.629 --> 00:22:00.256
I want you.

206
00:22:07.680 --> 00:22:11.475
♪ ♪

207
00:23:00.566 --> 00:23:03.360
♪ ♪

208
00:23:13.954 --> 00:23:16.791
(heavy breathing)

209
00:23:50.741 --> 00:23:54.537
♪ ♪

210
00:24:18.894 --> 00:24:20.604
(rumbling)

211
00:24:20.688 --> 00:24:22.523
(breathing heavily)

212
00:24:28.571 --> 00:24:30.030
(rumbling)

213
00:24:30.114 --> 00:24:32.199
(birds cawing)

214
00:24:40.374 --> 00:24:41.959
(rumbling)

215
00:24:57.391 --> 00:25:00.603
(Vhagar breathing deeply)

216
00:25:01.979 --> 00:25:04.315
(softly) Fuck.

217
00:25:16.452 --> 00:25:17.494
(Vhagar snorts)

218
00:25:39.475 --> 00:25:40.809
(exhales)

219
00:25:48.067 --> 00:25:50.653
(Vhagar breathing deeply)

220
00:26:01.038 --> 00:26:02.998
(tense music)

221
00:26:03.082 --> 00:26:04.333
(snarls)

222
00:26:07.670 --> 00:26:09.255
(growling)

223
00:26:22.559 --> 00:26:25.187
(Aemond breathing heavily)

224
00:26:27.898 --> 00:26:30.943
(snarls)

225
00:26:32.444 --> 00:26:35.947
(speaking High Valyrian)
<i>Dohaeras!</i>

226
00:26:35.948 --> 00:26:39.326
<i>Dohaeras. Vhagar! Lykiri!</i>

227
00:26:40.577 --> 00:26:41.078
<i>Lykiri!</i>

228
00:26:41.079 --> 00:26:43.956
(Vhagar quiets)

229
00:26:45.958 --> 00:26:48.002
<i>Lykiri.</i>

230
00:26:52.548 --> 00:26:53.590
(Vhagar inhales)

231
00:26:55.759 --> 00:26:57.303
(purrs)

232
00:27:01.890 --> 00:27:03.934
♪ ♪

233
00:27:09.315 --> 00:27:11.400
(breathing heavily)

234
00:27:14.111 --> 00:27:15.362
(grunts)

235
00:27:20.200 --> 00:27:23.037
(Vhagar grumbles)

236
00:27:36.759 --> 00:27:39.636
- (shouts) <i>Soves!</i>
- (grumbles)

237
00:27:40.304 --> 00:27:44.641
<i>Dohaeras. Vhagar! Soves!</i>

238
00:27:47.436 --> 00:27:48.812
Ah!

239
00:27:48.896 --> 00:27:51.022
(Vhagar vocalizes)

240
00:27:51.023 --> 00:27:53.150
(intense music)

241
00:27:53.817 --> 00:27:57.237
- Ah! Ahh!
- (roars)

242
00:28:08.040 --> 00:28:09.625
(roars)

243
00:28:13.337 --> 00:28:15.422
(Aemond yelling)

244
00:28:18.634 --> 00:28:20.219
(yelling)

245
00:28:24.681 --> 00:28:24.932
(roars)

246
00:28:24.933 --> 00:28:27.017
Ah!

247
00:28:27.476 --> 00:28:29.603
(groaning)

248
00:28:34.066 --> 00:28:36.110
(grunts)

249
00:28:37.778 --> 00:28:40.280
♪ ♪

250
00:28:40.364 --> 00:28:41.907
(yelling)

251
00:28:48.872 --> 00:28:50.457
(yelling)

252
00:28:50.916 --> 00:28:53.919
♪ ♪

253
00:29:15.649 --> 00:29:18.694
(yells)

254
00:29:29.121 --> 00:29:30.706
(yelling)

255
00:29:34.251 --> 00:29:35.251
Yeah! (laughs)

256
00:29:35.294 --> 00:29:39.089
♪ ♪

257
00:29:44.761 --> 00:29:46.346
(groaning)

258
00:29:58.984 --> 00:30:01.361
Baela: (whispers)
Jace. Jace.

259
00:30:01.445 --> 00:30:04.072
Jace. wake up. Wake up.

260
00:30:05.782 --> 00:30:08.869
- Someone stole Vhagar.
- (whispers) What?

261
00:30:19.755 --> 00:30:20.797
(Vhagar roars)

262
00:30:28.764 --> 00:30:31.808
- Rhaenyra: Who is it?
- (Vhagar roars)

263
00:30:44.821 --> 00:30:46.406
(grumbles)

264
00:30:53.497 --> 00:30:56.583
Lucerys:
Jace. what are we doing?

265
00:30:56.667 --> 00:30:57.917
- It's him.
- It's me.

266
00:30:57.918 --> 00:31:01.921
- Vhagar is my mother's dragon.
- Your mother's dead.

267
00:31:01.922 --> 00:31:03.650
- And Vhagar has a new rider now.
- She was mine to claim.

268
00:31:03.674 --> 00:31:06.301
Aemond:
Then you should've claimed her!

269
00:31:06.385 --> 00:31:08.636
Maybe your cousins
can find you a pig to ride.

270
00:31:08.637 --> 00:31:10.681
- It would suit you.

271
00:31:12.432 --> 00:31:13.976
- (grunts)
- (Aemond yells)

272
00:31:15.060 --> 00:31:17.937
Come at me again
and I'll feed you to my dragon!

273
00:31:17.938 --> 00:31:19.856
- (Jacaerys yells)
- (punches landing)

274
00:31:23.151 --> 00:31:24.652
(shrieks) Ah!

275
00:31:24.653 --> 00:31:27.155
(yells)

276
00:31:27.239 --> 00:31:28.824
(grunting. panting)

277
00:31:48.051 --> 00:31:49.677
(tense music)

278
00:31:49.678 --> 00:31:51.429
You will die screaming in flames

279
00:31:51.430 --> 00:31:53.139
just as your father did!

280
00:31:53.140 --> 00:31:54.432
Bastards.

281
00:31:54.433 --> 00:31:57.060
(crying)
My father's still alive.

282
00:31:57.144 --> 00:31:58.854
He doesn't know. does he.
Lord Strong?

283
00:32:02.232 --> 00:32:03.275
Jace!

284
00:32:08.447 --> 00:32:11.617
♪ ♪

285
00:32:19.458 --> 00:32:21.543
(Aemond wailing)

286
00:32:23.462 --> 00:32:25.440
- Harrold Westerling:
Cease this at once!
- (wailing)

287
00:32:25.464 --> 00:32:27.507
Get away!

288
00:32:30.093 --> 00:32:33.013
My Prince. my Prince.
Let me see.

289
00:32:34.056 --> 00:32:36.641
(Aemond breathing heavily)

290
00:32:36.642 --> 00:32:38.769
Gods be good.

291
00:32:39.936 --> 00:32:42.648
How could you allow
such a thing to happen?

292
00:32:44.816 --> 00:32:46.359
I will have answers.

293
00:32:46.360 --> 00:32:49.571
Harrold:
The princes were supposed
to be abed. My King.

294
00:32:49.655 --> 00:32:51.823
Viserys:
Who had the watch?

295
00:32:51.907 --> 00:32:54.617
Criston Cole:
Young prince was attacked by
his own cousins. Your Grace.

296
00:32:54.618 --> 00:32:57.870
You swore oaths to protect
and defend my blood!

297
00:32:57.871 --> 00:33:00.373
Westerling:
I'm very sorry. Your Grace.

298
00:33:00.374 --> 00:33:02.625
The Kingsguard has
never had to defend
princes from princes.

299
00:33:02.626 --> 00:33:03.918
- Your Grace.
- That is no answer!

300
00:33:03.919 --> 00:33:07.047
It will heal.
will it not. maester?

301
00:33:09.216 --> 00:33:10.676
Maester Kelvyn:
The flesh will heal.

302
00:33:12.803 --> 00:33:15.013
But the eye is lost. Your Grace.

303
00:33:18.266 --> 00:33:20.518
- Alicent: Where were you?
- Aegon: Me?

304
00:33:20.519 --> 00:33:22.353
- Ow! What was that for?
- That was nothing

305
00:33:22.354 --> 00:33:24.105
compared to the abuse
your brother suffered

306
00:33:24.106 --> 00:33:26.107
while you were drowning
in your cups. you fool.

307
00:33:26.108 --> 00:33:28.735
- (door opens)
- Corlys: What is
the meaning of this?

308
00:33:28.819 --> 00:33:31.237
Rhaenys:
Baela. Rhaena!

309
00:33:31.238 --> 00:33:32.364
What happened?

310
00:33:36.410 --> 00:33:38.537
Jace?

311
00:33:38.912 --> 00:33:40.414
Luke!

312
00:33:42.207 --> 00:33:44.500
- Show me. Show me.
- (cries)

313
00:33:44.501 --> 00:33:46.085
- Who did this?
- They attacked me!

314
00:33:46.086 --> 00:33:47.503
- He attacked Baela!
- He broke Luke's nose!

315
00:33:47.504 --> 00:33:51.800
(children shouting)

316
00:33:52.843 --> 00:33:55.803
Rhaena:
He stole my mother's dragon!

317
00:33:55.804 --> 00:33:57.972
- Enough.
- Lucerys: He was
gonna kill Jace!

318
00:33:57.973 --> 00:33:59.098
- I didn't do anything!
- Enough...

319
00:33:59.099 --> 00:34:00.642
It should be my son
telling the tale!

320
00:34:00.726 --> 00:34:02.644
- He called us...
- (yells) Silence!

321
00:34:06.356 --> 00:34:08.525
(whispers)
He called us bastards.

322
00:34:14.740 --> 00:34:16.783
Viserys: Aemond...

323
00:34:16.867 --> 00:34:18.660
I will have the truth
of what happened.

324
00:34:19.828 --> 00:34:22.789
- Now.
- What else is there to hear?

325
00:34:22.873 --> 00:34:23.998
Your son has been maimed.
Her son is responsible.

326
00:34:23.999 --> 00:34:27.085
- It was a regrettable accident.
- Alicent: Accident?

327
00:34:27.169 --> 00:34:28.544
The Prince Lucerys brought
a blade to the ambush.

328
00:34:28.545 --> 00:34:31.047
He meant to kill my son.

329
00:34:31.131 --> 00:34:32.799
It was my sons who were attacked

330
00:34:32.883 --> 00:34:36.427
and forced to defend themselves.

331
00:34:36.428 --> 00:34:38.471
Vile insults were
levied against them.

332
00:34:38.472 --> 00:34:40.098
What insults?

333
00:34:44.644 --> 00:34:48.064
The legitimacy
of my sons' birth was
put loudly to question.

334
00:34:48.148 --> 00:34:50.817
- What?
- He called us bastards.

335
00:34:55.739 --> 00:34:59.992
Rhaenyra:
My sons are in line to inherit
the Iron Throne. Your Grace.

336
00:34:59.993 --> 00:35:02.412
This is the highest of treasons.

337
00:35:03.914 --> 00:35:05.832
Prince Aemond must
be sharply questioned

338
00:35:05.916 --> 00:35:08.877
so we might learn where
he heard such slanders.

339
00:35:10.378 --> 00:35:11.922
Over an insult?

340
00:35:12.756 --> 00:35:15.050
My son has lost an eye.

341
00:35:17.719 --> 00:35:20.680
You tell me. boy.
Where did you hear this lie?

342
00:35:20.764 --> 00:35:22.325
Alicent: The insult was
training yard bluster.

343
00:35:22.349 --> 00:35:24.684
- The lot of boys.
It was nothing.
- Aemond...

344
00:35:24.768 --> 00:35:26.436
I asked you a question.

345
00:35:29.564 --> 00:35:32.567
Where is Ser Laenor. I wonder?
The boys' father?

346
00:35:32.651 --> 00:35:34.610
Perhaps he might have
something to say in the matter.

347
00:35:34.611 --> 00:35:36.237
Yes. Where is Ser Laenor?

348
00:35:36.238 --> 00:35:40.783
I do not know. Your Grace.
I... could not find sleep.

349
00:35:40.784 --> 00:35:42.869
I had gone out to walk.

350
00:35:42.953 --> 00:35:45.121
Entertaining
his young squires.
I would venture.

351
00:35:49.251 --> 00:35:50.335
Viserys: Aemond...

352
00:35:51.878 --> 00:35:54.923
look at me.

353
00:35:55.465 --> 00:35:57.550
Your king demands an answer.

354
00:35:57.551 --> 00:35:59.761
Who spoke these lies to you?

355
00:36:00.971 --> 00:36:02.055
(tense music)

356
00:36:17.237 --> 00:36:18.530
It was Aegon.

357
00:36:21.324 --> 00:36:24.369
Me?

358
00:36:24.911 --> 00:36:26.204
And you. boy?

359
00:36:30.000 --> 00:36:33.377
Where did you hear
such calumnies?

360
00:36:33.378 --> 00:36:36.172
(yells) Aegon!
Tell me the truth of it!

361
00:36:38.717 --> 00:36:41.344
We know. Father.

362
00:36:43.138 --> 00:36:45.181
Everyone knows.

363
00:36:46.683 --> 00:36:48.310
Just look at them.

364
00:36:49.936 --> 00:36:52.981
♪ ♪

365
00:37:05.201 --> 00:37:07.537
This interminable
infighting must cease!

366
00:37:07.621 --> 00:37:09.956
All of you!

367
00:37:11.625 --> 00:37:14.419
We are family!

368
00:37:19.132 --> 00:37:23.135
Now make your apologies
and show good will
to one another.

369
00:37:23.136 --> 00:37:26.222
Your father. your grandsire.
your king demands it!

370
00:37:31.561 --> 00:37:34.606
♪ ♪

371
00:37:42.364 --> 00:37:43.990
That is insufficient.

372
00:37:46.910 --> 00:37:48.953
Aemond has been damaged.
permanently. My King.

373
00:37:48.954 --> 00:37:50.621
"Good will" cannot
make him whole.

374
00:37:50.622 --> 00:37:52.874
I know. Alicent.

375
00:37:52.958 --> 00:37:54.458
but I cannot restore his eye.

376
00:37:54.459 --> 00:37:56.294
No. because it's been taken.

377
00:37:56.378 --> 00:37:59.881
- What would you have me do?
- There is a debt to be paid.

378
00:38:03.301 --> 00:38:06.304
- I shall have one of her
son's eyes in return.
- (murmuring)

379
00:38:08.765 --> 00:38:12.143
- My dear wife.
- He is your son. Viserys.

380
00:38:12.227 --> 00:38:12.686
Your blood.

381
00:38:12.687 --> 00:38:14.186
Viserys:
Do not...

382
00:38:14.187 --> 00:38:18.483
allow your temper
to guide your judgment.

383
00:38:24.280 --> 00:38:27.074
Alicent: If the King
will not seek justice.
the Queen will.

384
00:38:27.075 --> 00:38:28.243
Ser Criston...

385
00:38:29.744 --> 00:38:31.663
bring me the eye
of Lucerys Velaryon.

386
00:38:32.455 --> 00:38:33.164
- Mother!
- Viserys: Alicent.

387
00:38:33.248 --> 00:38:34.248
He can choose which eye to keep.

388
00:38:34.249 --> 00:38:35.875
a privilege he did
not grant my son.

389
00:38:35.959 --> 00:38:38.211
You will do no such thing.

390
00:38:38.295 --> 00:38:41.006
- Stay your hand.
- No. you are sworn to me!

391
00:38:45.385 --> 00:38:47.512
As your protector. my Queen.

392
00:38:50.557 --> 00:38:54.685
Alicent. this matter...
is finished.

393
00:38:54.686 --> 00:38:56.354
Do you understand?

394
00:38:57.897 --> 00:39:00.942
♪ ♪

395
00:39:08.616 --> 00:39:09.576
And let it be known:

396
00:39:09.577 --> 00:39:12.244
anyone whose tongue dares
to question the birth

397
00:39:12.245 --> 00:39:14.580
of Princess Rhaenyra's sons

398
00:39:14.581 --> 00:39:16.750
should have it removed.

399
00:39:19.627 --> 00:39:22.672
Thank you. Father.

400
00:39:31.931 --> 00:39:33.993
- Harrold: Your Grace.
Stay with the King!
- Viserys: Alicent!

401
00:39:34.017 --> 00:39:35.601
- Criston:
Hold your approach!
- (screams)

402
00:39:35.602 --> 00:39:37.436
- Harrold: Do not. Ser Criston!
- Viserys: Alicent!

403
00:39:37.437 --> 00:39:39.188
- (screaming)
- Do not. Ser Criston!

404
00:39:39.189 --> 00:39:41.148
Viserys: Alicent!

405
00:39:41.149 --> 00:39:43.275
- Rhaenyra: No!
- (grunts)

406
00:39:43.276 --> 00:39:45.278
Harrold:
Stay your hand. Cole!

407
00:39:46.821 --> 00:39:48.280
You've gone too far.

408
00:39:48.281 --> 00:39:49.615
I?

409
00:39:49.616 --> 00:39:51.993
What have I done
but what was expected
of me?

410
00:39:53.244 --> 00:39:56.664
Forever upholding
the kingdom.
the family. the law.

411
00:39:58.333 --> 00:40:01.293
- While you flout all
to do as you please.
- Alicent. let her go!

412
00:40:01.294 --> 00:40:03.963
Where is duty?
Where is sacrifice?

413
00:40:04.047 --> 00:40:05.840
It's trampled under
your pretty foot again.

414
00:40:05.924 --> 00:40:08.009
Release the blade. Alicent.

415
00:40:08.093 --> 00:40:10.302
And now you take my son's eye.

416
00:40:10.303 --> 00:40:11.971
and to even that.
you feel entitled.

417
00:40:12.055 --> 00:40:14.265
Exhausting. wasn't it?

418
00:40:14.349 --> 00:40:17.309
Hiding beneath the cloak
of your own righteousness.

419
00:40:17.310 --> 00:40:21.147
(whispers) But now
they see you as you are.

420
00:40:21.231 --> 00:40:22.524
(grunts)

421
00:40:32.742 --> 00:40:35.787
♪ ♪

422
00:40:58.101 --> 00:41:00.978
Do not mourn me. Mother.

423
00:41:00.979 --> 00:41:02.939
It was a fair exchange.

424
00:41:03.648 --> 00:41:06.025
I may have lost an eye...

425
00:41:07.527 --> 00:41:09.362
but I gained a dragon.

426
00:41:17.871 --> 00:41:19.998
This proceeding is at an end.

427
00:41:42.187 --> 00:41:45.231
♪ ♪

428
00:41:57.160 --> 00:41:59.496
The Hand. Your Grace.

429
00:42:15.011 --> 00:42:16.762
(door closes)

430
00:42:16.763 --> 00:42:18.722
Say your piece.

431
00:42:18.723 --> 00:42:20.892
Now. what piece is that?

432
00:42:23.895 --> 00:42:26.730
I've conducted myself
in a manner...

433
00:42:26.731 --> 00:42:28.900
unbefitting my station.

434
00:42:30.401 --> 00:42:31.736
Or any other.

435
00:42:35.156 --> 00:42:36.741
I lost composure...

436
00:42:38.868 --> 00:42:41.913
assaulted the Princess.

437
00:42:42.705 --> 00:42:46.251
Already the word is spreading.
the gossip speculating
that I've gone mad.

438
00:42:47.085 --> 00:42:49.545
All true.

439
00:42:49.629 --> 00:42:51.256
I disgraced myself.

440
00:42:53.383 --> 00:42:56.928
And ensured
my husband's favor will
forever rest on her.

441
00:42:58.429 --> 00:42:59.889
Otto Hightower:
And yet...

442
00:43:01.015 --> 00:43:03.476
I've never seen that side
of you. my daughter.

443
00:43:06.437 --> 00:43:08.981
I even doubted its existence.

444
00:43:08.982 --> 00:43:12.568
- It was an ugly thing.
I regret it.
- We play an ugly game.

445
00:43:14.445 --> 00:43:15.821
And now. for the first time.

446
00:43:15.822 --> 00:43:19.367
I see that you have
the determination
to win it.

447
00:43:23.162 --> 00:43:26.332
- Rhaenyra...
- You see her for what she is.

448
00:43:26.416 --> 00:43:29.377
What the King's
stubbornness has wrought.

449
00:43:32.588 --> 00:43:36.009
- What will he say to me?
- He'll forgive you.

450
00:43:37.135 --> 00:43:39.512
What else can he do?

451
00:43:40.930 --> 00:43:43.515
Now go to him. be penitent.

452
00:43:43.516 --> 00:43:46.185
plead the injury to your son.

453
00:43:46.269 --> 00:43:49.188
Keep a grip on your passions.

454
00:43:49.272 --> 00:43:53.443
And I promise you.
in time. you and I
together will prevail.

455
00:43:56.612 --> 00:43:58.656
What that rogue Aemond has done

456
00:43:58.740 --> 00:44:01.409
in winning Vhagar to our side.

457
00:44:03.161 --> 00:44:04.787
The boy was right.

458
00:44:04.871 --> 00:44:08.124
It's worth a thousand times
the price he paid.

459
00:44:21.971 --> 00:44:23.806
(Rhaenyra winces)

460
00:44:32.148 --> 00:44:33.274
Mm.

461
00:44:34.484 --> 00:44:38.654
You will scar.
but the wound will heal.

462
00:44:39.947 --> 00:44:42.491
Valyrian steel cuts clean.

463
00:44:42.492 --> 00:44:44.160
(door opens)

464
00:44:49.040 --> 00:44:50.833
Gods.

465
00:44:53.127 --> 00:44:54.753
Is everyone all right?

466
00:44:54.754 --> 00:44:56.547
Maester Kelvyn:
A broken nose is the worst.

467
00:44:56.631 --> 00:44:58.007
Thank you. maester.

468
00:44:58.674 --> 00:44:59.759
Leave us.

469
00:45:03.096 --> 00:45:04.680
You as well.

470
00:45:04.764 --> 00:45:08.517
You've already found
enough trouble today.

471
00:45:08.518 --> 00:45:09.644
Yes. Mother.

472
00:45:17.693 --> 00:45:18.486
Laenor:
I should've been there.

473
00:45:18.487 --> 00:45:21.447
Those should be our house words.

474
00:45:23.533 --> 00:45:27.202
I have fought dreadful enemies.

475
00:45:27.203 --> 00:45:29.872
but I could not defend
my dear sister

476
00:45:29.956 --> 00:45:32.083
far from home and in agony.

477
00:45:33.501 --> 00:45:35.628
- I could not defend you.
- Sit down.

478
00:45:47.348 --> 00:45:49.725
Aemond called our sons bastards.

479
00:45:54.730 --> 00:45:55.481
(sighs)

480
00:45:55.565 --> 00:45:58.234
I have failed you. Rhaenyra.

481
00:45:58.734 --> 00:46:00.986
Our marriage...

482
00:46:00.987 --> 00:46:03.239
I tried.

483
00:46:05.408 --> 00:46:06.701
Our boys...

484
00:46:08.411 --> 00:46:09.995
- I do love them.
- I know.

485
00:46:09.996 --> 00:46:11.497
Deeply.

486
00:46:14.500 --> 00:46:17.378
But I have not. mayhaps...

487
00:46:19.005 --> 00:46:20.339
loved them enough.

488
00:46:26.262 --> 00:46:28.723
I had hoped to bear
your children.

489
00:46:30.433 --> 00:46:32.560
The few times we lay together.

490
00:46:36.272 --> 00:46:38.191
Things might've been different.

491
00:46:41.652 --> 00:46:44.864
I hate the gods
for making me as they did.

492
00:46:45.281 --> 00:46:47.449
I do not.

493
00:46:47.450 --> 00:46:49.911
You are an honorable man

494
00:46:51.120 --> 00:46:54.164
with a good heart.

495
00:46:54.165 --> 00:46:56.375
(chuckles)
It's a rare thing.

496
00:47:01.797 --> 00:47:03.437
We made an arrangement
all those years ago

497
00:47:03.466 --> 00:47:05.801
to do our duty and...

498
00:47:07.970 --> 00:47:09.805
yet explore happiness.

499
00:47:11.682 --> 00:47:13.226
(laughing)

500
00:47:16.979 --> 00:47:19.189
- (laughs)
- But there are times

501
00:47:19.190 --> 00:47:22.527
I think when these things
cannot mutually exist.

502
00:47:25.488 --> 00:47:29.534
Ser Qarl will return
soon to the fighting
in the Stepstones.

503
00:47:31.285 --> 00:47:33.412
But I recommit myself to you.

504
00:47:34.956 --> 00:47:39.543
And to strengthening
our house as we prepare you
for your ascension.

505
00:47:39.544 --> 00:47:42.796
I will raise our sons
to be princes of the realm.

506
00:47:42.797 --> 00:47:45.424
- Laenor...
- You deserve better
than what I have been.

507
00:47:48.177 --> 00:47:50.012
You deserve a husband.

508
00:48:01.065 --> 00:48:03.859
♪ ♪

509
00:48:10.283 --> 00:48:12.284
I've asked them
to have wine ready
for you on the ship.

510
00:48:12.285 --> 00:48:14.453
To help you sleep.

511
00:48:19.041 --> 00:48:20.876
(Viserys groans)

512
00:48:23.045 --> 00:48:24.630
I'm so sorry.

513
00:48:27.466 --> 00:48:28.634
Viserys...

514
00:48:28.718 --> 00:48:29.844
We will speak no more of it.

515
00:48:33.556 --> 00:48:36.016
(breathing heavily)

516
00:48:36.017 --> 00:48:38.894
♪ ♪

517
00:48:41.230 --> 00:48:43.065
(birds cawing)

518
00:49:00.875 --> 00:49:01.917
♪ ♪

519
00:49:04.128 --> 00:49:05.212
(roars)

520
00:49:25.274 --> 00:49:28.319
♪ ♪

521
00:49:36.911 --> 00:49:37.995
(dragon vocalizing)

522
00:49:46.754 --> 00:49:48.881
Fire is such strange power.

523
00:49:53.302 --> 00:49:55.888
Everything that House Targaryen
possesses is owed to it.

524
00:49:58.808 --> 00:50:01.268
Yet it has cost us both
what we loved.

525
00:50:03.020 --> 00:50:04.771
Perhaps the Velaryons
knew the truth of it.

526
00:50:04.772 --> 00:50:05.981
The sea is the better ally.

527
00:50:08.317 --> 00:50:10.402
Fire is a prison.

528
00:50:10.403 --> 00:50:12.905
The sea offers an escape.

529
00:50:22.164 --> 00:50:23.642
Larys Strong:
A perversion of justice.

530
00:50:23.666 --> 00:50:26.293
The young prince...

531
00:50:26.377 --> 00:50:27.712
defiled.

532
00:50:29.171 --> 00:50:30.423
An outrage.

533
00:50:32.341 --> 00:50:33.759
Indeed.

534
00:50:37.388 --> 00:50:38.180
If it's an eye you want

535
00:50:38.264 --> 00:50:41.809
to balance the scales.
I am your servant.

536
00:50:46.731 --> 00:50:48.774
That will not be necessary.

537
00:50:51.652 --> 00:50:53.252
But your devotion
has not gone unnoticed.

538
00:50:54.697 --> 00:50:57.658
These are dangerous times.

539
00:51:01.370 --> 00:51:05.374
The day will doubtless come
when I require such a friend.

540
00:51:06.876 --> 00:51:10.337
With not only skill
but discretion as well.

541
00:51:13.174 --> 00:51:16.343
I shall await your call.
my Queen.

542
00:51:31.525 --> 00:51:34.361
I need you. Uncle.

543
00:51:43.412 --> 00:51:45.289
(speaking High Valyrian)

544
00:52:36.799 --> 00:52:39.760
We could not marry
unless Laenor were dead.

545
00:52:40.469 --> 00:52:43.264
♪ ♪

546
00:52:45.140 --> 00:52:46.433
I know.

547
00:52:56.110 --> 00:52:57.736
(indistinct chatter)

548
00:52:59.363 --> 00:53:03.825
I've heard about
your exploits
in the Stepstones.

549
00:53:03.826 --> 00:53:05.869
Ser Qarl.

550
00:53:05.870 --> 00:53:07.829
Said to be a knight
of remarkable skill.

551
00:53:07.830 --> 00:53:10.582
You flatter me. m'lord.

552
00:53:10.583 --> 00:53:13.251
But alas. common-born.

553
00:53:13.252 --> 00:53:16.880
You're a landless knight
with a lord's taste.

554
00:53:16.881 --> 00:53:18.799
Ser Laenor's been kind to me.

555
00:53:20.509 --> 00:53:21.886
Do you know...

556
00:53:24.346 --> 00:53:27.224
there are places across
the Narrow Sea...

557
00:53:27.308 --> 00:53:31.853
where it doesn't matter
what a man's name is?

558
00:53:31.854 --> 00:53:34.607
Only how much gold he possesses.

559
00:53:38.027 --> 00:53:39.347
What are you asking
of me. m'lord?

560
00:53:40.696 --> 00:53:42.323
A quick death.

561
00:53:43.949 --> 00:53:45.576
One with witnesses.

562
00:53:46.660 --> 00:53:49.705
(Qarl scoffs)

563
00:53:50.623 --> 00:53:54.376
♪ ♪

564
00:53:54.460 --> 00:53:57.295
Rhaenyra:
<i>I will not be a tyrant.</i>

565
00:53:57.296 --> 00:53:59.965
- And rule through terror.
- (door opens)

566
00:54:00.049 --> 00:54:01.842
Daemon:
<i>A tyrant rules
only through terror.</i>

567
00:54:01.926 --> 00:54:04.762
- (grunting)
- Shh.

568
00:54:05.679 --> 00:54:06.972
(neck snaps)

569
00:54:08.599 --> 00:54:11.143
Daemon:
<i>If the King isn't feared.
he is powerless.</i>

570
00:54:12.227 --> 00:54:13.455
<i>If you are to be a strong queen.</i>

571
00:54:13.479 --> 00:54:15.313
<i>you must cultivate
love and respect. yes.</i>

572
00:54:15.314 --> 00:54:18.108
<i>but your subjects must fear you.</i>

573
00:54:18.192 --> 00:54:19.818
Who let you in here?

574
00:54:23.405 --> 00:54:25.658
Why are you in my father's hall?

575
00:54:28.577 --> 00:54:30.662
♪ ♪

576
00:54:30.663 --> 00:54:32.665
You have always
looked down on me.

577
00:54:33.916 --> 00:54:35.250
Rhaenyra:
<i>I do love Laenor.</i>

578
00:54:35.334 --> 00:54:38.212
Daemon:
<i>Then grant him this kindness.</i>

579
00:54:39.296 --> 00:54:40.505
<i>Set him free.</i>

580
00:54:40.506 --> 00:54:43.634
You forget yourself.

581
00:54:44.259 --> 00:54:46.178
- My lord. Please!
- (grunting)

582
00:54:52.559 --> 00:54:52.893
I'll alert the guards!

583
00:54:52.977 --> 00:54:56.146
(intense music)

584
00:54:56.230 --> 00:54:58.857
(grunting. yelling)

585
00:55:02.778 --> 00:55:06.031
Rhaenyra:
<i>This will cost Lord Corlys
and Princess Rhaenys</i>

586
00:55:06.115 --> 00:55:07.241
<i>their only remaining child.</i>

587
00:55:11.328 --> 00:55:14.373
<i>And the realm will whisper
that I was somehow responsible.</i>

588
00:55:16.458 --> 00:55:18.168
(Rhaenys crying)

589
00:55:18.252 --> 00:55:19.711
(yells) No!

590
00:55:19.712 --> 00:55:20.546
Daemon:
<i>Let them whisper.</i>

591
00:55:20.547 --> 00:55:23.507
No!

592
00:55:25.551 --> 00:55:26.843
(shouts)
How did you let this happen?

593
00:55:26.844 --> 00:55:28.929
In my fucking hall?

594
00:55:29.013 --> 00:55:30.180
Tell me!

595
00:55:30.264 --> 00:55:30.764
Daemon:
<i>We will know the truth of it</i>

596
00:55:30.848 --> 00:55:34.351
<i>and our enemies won't.</i>

597
00:55:34.435 --> 00:55:37.396
They will fear what else
we might be capable of.

598
00:55:38.897 --> 00:55:41.942
(light music)

599
00:55:42.026 --> 00:55:45.070
♪ ♪

600
00:56:05.174 --> 00:56:07.843
(Priest speaking High Valyrian)

601
00:56:23.609 --> 00:56:25.444
(Priest continues)

602
00:56:36.872 --> 00:56:39.917
♪ ♪

603
00:57:07.069 --> 00:57:08.612
(panting)

604
00:57:25.212 --> 00:57:28.257
♪ ♪

605
00:58:00.789 --> 00:58:04.585
♪ ♪

605
00:58:05.305 --> 00:59:05.760
Do you want subtitles for any video?
